article.headline: Kansas 70, Sacramento State 64
article.story:
EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Tamara Ransburg scored 18 points to lead
Kansas past Sacramento State 70-64 at the Oregon Classic on
Saturday.

Crystal Kemp added 13 points for the Jayhawks (1-2), and Blair
Waltz scored 10. Led by Ransburg, who was 6 for 8 from the field,
Kansas shot 47 percent for the game.

Katelyn Ciampi paced the Hornets (0-4) with 13 points, while
Sarah Craig had 12.

The Jayhawks led 64-44 with 9:14 left in the game before a 16-0
run by the Hornets cut the lead to four with 1:10 to play.

Ciampi scored eight of her points during that stretch.

The Jayhawks, however, made 8-of-9 free throws in the final 44
seconds to seal their first win of the season.

Kemp scored 11 of her 13 points in the first half to give the
Jayhawks a 40-31 lead at the break. A 9-0 run in the opening
minutes of the second half put them up 49-31.
